               <textBox id="scope">
                  <label>Principal property involved and scope of problem</label>
                  <p>In the course of interviewing Japanese</p>
				  <p>the similarity of arangements for storage of automobiles</p>
				  <p>lead to questioning as to the details.</p>
				  <p>It developed that the subject company had made</p>
				  <p>an attractive dead storage offer.  The rates quoted were</p>
				  <p>$30.00 for the 1st yr., $25.00 for the 2nd yr., &amp; $22.50 for the 3rd yr.</p>
				  <p>In addition to the first year's charge there was work</p>
				  <p>done on the car such as removing battery, draining radiator, etc.</p>
               </textBox>
               <textBox id="action">
                  <label>Action taken</label>
                  <p><note>continuation from previous section</note>that cost the Japanese about $9.50 additional</p>
				  <p>Some of the cars stored as above were also</p>
				  <p>subject to sale at a price set by the owner.</p>
				  <p>(over)<note>more text written on the back of the form, port_01_017_page9.pdf</note></p>
				  <p>Evidently the standing of this company in</p>
				  <p>the community was such that the Japanese felt</p>
				  <p>entirely satisfied with the arrangements.</p>
				  <p>undoubtedly to a lesser extent other comapnies</p>
				  <p>in Flood River must be doing similar storage.</p>
				  <p>No endeavor was made in the first instance</p>
				  <p>to check the number of such storages as it was</p>
				  <p>not until the name<orgNmae project-ref="JAIFRP-0016">"Bartol"</orgNmae>became familiar</p>
				  <p>through repetition that more definite inquiry</p>
				  <p>was made.  Suffice it to say that the</p>
				  <p>number was enough to be noticeable to an</p>
				  <p>interviewer handling people one at a time only</p>
				  <p>a portion of whom were storing their cars.</p>
				  <p><note>signature of agent</note><span type="uncertainty" cause="handwriting"/><person role="4" wra-ref="" project-ref="JAIFRP-00024">Schmeer</person></p>
